{"parse":{"title":"Mathematics mastery","pageid":51056252,"revid":846931126,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Mathematics mastery</b> is an approach to <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematics_education\" title=\"Mathematics education\">mathematics education</a> which is based on <a href=\"/wiki/Mastery_learning\" title=\"Mastery learning\">mastery learning</a> in which most students are expected to achieve a high level of competence before progressing.  This technique is used in countries such as China and <a href=\"/wiki/Singapore_math\" title=\"Singapore math\">Singapore</a> where good results have been achieved and so the approach is now being promoted in the <a href=\"/wiki/UK\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UK\">UK</a> by people such as schools minister <a href=\"/wiki/Nick_Gibb\" title=\"Nick Gibb\">Nick Gibb</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BBC_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BBC-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NCETM_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NCETM-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-MM_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MM-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TES_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TES-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  Chinese teachers were brought to the UK to demonstrate the Shanghai mastery approach in 2015.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G2_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G2-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  A trial was made in the UK with about 10,000 students of ages 5\u20136 and 11\u201312.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  In one year, test scores indicated that the students were about a month ahead of students in schools using other approaches.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> This result was considered small but significant.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The National Association of Mathematics Advisers has highlighted five issues in understanding this approach.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NAMA_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NAMA-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ol><li>Variation in the methods promoted by different organisations</li>\n<li>The extent of <a href=\"/wiki/Differentiated_instruction\" title=\"Differentiated instruction\">differentiation</a></li>\n<li>The content of the <a href=\"/wiki/Curriculum\" title=\"Curriculum\">curriculum</a></li>\n<li>The amount of practise and repetition</li>\n<li>The choice and use of textbooks</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mathematics_mastery&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-BBC-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-BBC_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/education-36772954\"><i>Asian maths method offered to schools</i></a>, BBC, 12 July 2016</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Asian+maths+method+offered+to+schools&amp;rft.pub=BBC&amp;rft.date=2016-07-12&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Feducation-36772954&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematics+mastery\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-NCETM-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-NCETM_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.ncetm.org.uk/resources/47230\"><i>Mastery</i></a>, <a href=\"/wiki/National_Centre_for_Excellence_in_the_Teaching_of_Mathematics\" title=\"National Centre for Excellence in the Teaching of Mathematics\">National Centre for Excellence in the Teaching of Mathematics</a>, 1 July 2016</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mastery&amp;rft.pub=National+Centre+for+Excellence+in+the+Teaching+of+Mathematics&amp;rft.date=2016-07-01&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncetm.org.uk%2Fresources%2F47230&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematics+mastery\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-MM-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-MM_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFDrury2014\" class=\"citation\">Drury, Helen (2014), <i>Mastering Mathematics</i>, Oxford University Press, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780198351757\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780198351757\">9780198351757</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mastering+Mathematics&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=9780198351757&amp;rft.aulast=Drury&amp;rft.aufirst=Helen&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematics+mastery\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-TES-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-TES_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFSarah_Cunnane2015\" class=\"citation\">Sarah Cunnane (27 March 2015), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.tes.com/news/school-news/breaking-news/schools-mi